@startuml
title Chapter 13 - Fundamental Cloud Architectures (Overview)

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/package-diagram-style.iuml

package "Fundamental Cloud Architectures" as FCA {

  package "Scaling and Distribution" as SD {
    rectangle "Workload\nDistribution" as WD
    rectangle "Dynamic\nScalability" as DS
    rectangle "Elastic Resource\nCapacity" as ERC
    rectangle "Service Load\nBalancing" as SLB
    rectangle "Cloud\nBursting" as CB
  }

  package "Resource Organization" as RO {
    rectangle "Resource\nPooling" as RP
  }

  package "Storage" as ST {
    rectangle "Elastic Disk\nProvisioning" as EDP
    rectangle "Redundant\nStorage" as RS
  }

  package "Cloud Topology" as CT {
    rectangle "Multicloud" as MC
  }
}

WD .down.> SLB : specialized\nvariation
DS .down.> ERC : vertical\nvariation
RP .right.> DS : supplies\npools
RP .right.> ERC : supplies\nCPU/RAM pools
CB .down.> WD : burst-out uses\nredundant resources

note bottom of FCA
  Each architecture documents the typical
  involvement of cloud computing mechanisms
  introduced in Part II.
end note

@enduml

